@mfussenegger Is there a performance penalty for storing the "kind/type" in the event data, rather than in the pattern you filter against?

I would assume that this:
```lua
vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd("Progress", {
  pattern = "lsp",
  callback = function() ... end,
})
```
would be faster than this:
```lua
vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd("Progress", {
  callback = function(args)
    if args.data.type ~= "lsp" then
      return
    end
    ...
  end,
})
```

If there is a (noticeable) penalty, would it be worth it to change the `Progress` event to have the `pattern` match against some sort of "progress source" rather than the title?
